Hi, Amber.

As Amber wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/09/2004 at 15:53:37 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>Change each measurement to the smaller unit. For some problems, you 
>may  need to change the units twice.
>
>8 1/2pt=__c
>
>[Difficulty]
>everything, i dont understand it
>
>[Thoughts]
>2 pt= 1 quart
>8 ounces =1 cup

The fact you need here is one you left out:

  2 cups = 1 pint

So you can replace the word "pint" with "2 cups":

  8 1/2 pints = 8 1/2 times 1 pint = 8 1/2 times 2 cups

Can you finish?

Here is more help on working with units:

 http://mathforum.org/library/drmath/sets/select/dm_unit_convert.html

 http://mathforum.org/library/drmath/sets/select/dm_tsp_oz.html

If you have any further questions, feel free to write back.


